Almost found out the cause: `@kilocode/cli` announces v1.x. But the real latest is v7.x.

Somewhere in the code force itself to upgrade to npm latest tag, immediately after the first install, which should be v7.x.

User types `npm install -g @kilocode/cli` will quickly install twice, and eventually to v7.x.

[npm config get registry](https://github.com/Kilo-Org/kilocode/blob/main/packages/opencode/src/installation/index.ts#L220)

[KILO_DISABLE_AUTOUPDATE](https://github.com/Kilo-Org/kilocode/blob/main/packages/opencode/src/flag/flag.ts#L13)

# Requirements

How to install if the npm registry mirror is broken?

# Design

Override registry when install, so it will install twice and install the correct version v7.x.

Global disable auto-update, so it will not install wrong versions.

# Tasks

## [ ] TASK-001 System Global - Disable auto update
KILO_DISABLE_AUTOUPDATE=1

## [ ] TASK-002 Current Console Tab - Override npm registry and install
-- Mac / iTerm2
NPM_CONFIG_REGISTRY=https://registry.npmjs.org/ npm install -g @kilocode/cli

-- Windows / PowerShell
$env:NPM_CONFIG_REGISTRY="https://registry.npmjs.org/"
npm install -g @kilocode/cli

## [ ] TASK-003 New Console Tab - Verify
kilocode --version
7.x

